text: Missy is a former commune in the Calvados department in the Normandy region in northwestern France. On 1 January 2016, it was merged into the new commune of Noyers-Missy,Arrêté préfectoral 9 December 2015 which became part of the new commune Val d'Arry on 1 January 2017. ==Population== ==See also== *Communes of the Calvados department ==References== Category:Former communes of Calvados (department) Category:Calvados communes articles needing translation from French Wikipedia Category:Communes in Normandy
